{
  "name": "Permit Application Classifier",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## \ud83c\udfd7\ufe0f Permit Application Classifier\n\n### What this workflow does\n1. Watches Google Drive for permit application PDFs\n2. Extracts all application details and project info\n3. AI classifies complexity and checks completeness\n4. Routes to three paths based on classification:\n   - COMPLETE: Fast-track approval notification\n   - NEEDS INFO: Auto-request for missing documents\n   - REJECTED: Denial notice with reasons\n5. Logs all applications to Google Sheets\n\n### Setup steps\n1. Get PDF Vector API key from pdfvector.com/api-keys\n2. Create a Google Drive folder for permit applications\n3. Create a Google Sheet with these columns:\n   Application # | Date | Applicant | Permit Type | Address | Value | Complexity | Zoning Check | Env Review | Route To | Est. Days | Processed\n4. Update YOUR_FOLDER_ID in the Google Drive Trigger node\n5. Update YOUR_SPREADSHEET_ID in the Log to Sheets nodes\n6. Update YOUR_SLACK_CHANNEL_ID in the Slack nodes\n7. Connect Google Drive, Google Sheets, PDF Vector, and Slack credentials\n\n### Classification Logic\n- COMPLETE: All required docs present, meets zoning\n- NEEDS INFO: Missing documents or unclear details\n- REJECTED: Zoning violation or ineligible application\n\n### Perfect for\n- Municipal permit offices\n- Building departments\n- Planning departments",
        "height": 600,
        "width": 440,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "sticky-main",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        60,
        60
      ]
    },
